(7, 'FACTS ABOUT EGYPT', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p>What do you know about Egypt? It&rsquo;s home to one of the world&rsquo;s oldest civilizations and the 29th largest country in the world by area with more than 82 million inhabitants.</p>\r\n<p>Many dreams about visiting the Pyramids of Egypt, but there&rsquo;s more than Pyramids to explore and see. Here are 10 interesting facts about Egypt!</p>\r\n<h2>1. THE EGYPTIANS INVENTED THE 365-DAYS A YEAR CALENDAR</h2>\r\n<p>Yes, the ancient Egyptians invented the 365-days a year calendar, to predict the yearly floodings of the Nile river.</p>\r\n<div><img style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" srcset=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world-66x66.jpg 66w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world-200x199.jpg 200w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world-300x300.jpg 300w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world-400x399.jpg 400w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world-600x598.jpg 600w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world.jpg 750w\" alt=\"oldest calendar in the world\" width=\"750\" height=\"748\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world.jpg\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world-66x66.jpg 66w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world-200x199.jpg 200w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world-300x300.jpg 300w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world-400x399.jpg 400w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world-600x598.jpg 600w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/oldest-calendar-in-the-world.jpg 750w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" data-was-processed=\"true\" />\r\n<p>Photo: Shutterstock</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>2.&nbsp;WORLD&rsquo;S OLDEST DRESS WAS FOUND HERE. 5000 YEARS OLD</h2>\r\n<p>How cool is that? Egypt may be home to the world&rsquo;s first fashion house. I wonder if they had their own brand as well?</p>\r\n<h2>3. THE GREAT PYRAMIDS WAS NOT BUILT BY SLAVES</h2>\r\n<p>Many people believe the pyramids were being built by slaves, but that&rsquo;s is not the case. They were paid laborers, and most of them built with great honor towards the Pharao and those who died were buried in the tombs near the sacred pyramids.</p>\r\n<div>READ MORE:&nbsp;&nbsp;15 Reasons to Visit Egypt</div>\r\n<p><img style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/giza-pyramids-from-above.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" srcset=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/giza-pyramids-from-above-200x132.jpg 200w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/giza-pyramids-from-above-300x198.jpg 300w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/giza-pyramids-from-above-400x264.jpg 400w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/giza-pyramids-from-above-600x395.jpg 600w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/giza-pyramids-from-above.jpg 730w\" alt=\"giza pyramids from above\" width=\"730\" height=\"481\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/giza-pyramids-from-above.jpg\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/giza-pyramids-from-above-200x132.jpg 200w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/giza-pyramids-from-above-300x198.jpg 300w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/giza-pyramids-from-above-400x264.jpg 400w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/giza-pyramids-from-above-600x395.jpg 600w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/giza-pyramids-from-above.jpg 730w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" data-was-processed=\"true\" /></p>\r\n<h2>4. GREATER CAIRO IS THE LARGEST CITY IN AFRICA AND THE MIDDLE EAST</h2>\r\n<p>With an estimated population of 22 million and approximately 500 square km, Cairo is the largest city in Africa and the Middle East.</p>\r\n<h2>5.&nbsp;THERE ARE 5 MILLION FACEBOOK USERS IN EGYPT</h2>\r\n<p>That&rsquo;s a lot of Facebook users, and it&rsquo;s continuously&nbsp;growing. Five million users make it the most active Facebook community in the Middle East.</p>\r\n<h2>6.&nbsp;THE MOST POPULAR SPORT IN EGYPT IS FOOTBALL</h2>\r\n<p>Another fun fact about Egyptian football. There are two teams that are fierce rivals, but still sharing the same stadium, much like in Italy were A.C Milan and Inter are sharing the same stadium, even though they are rivals!</p>\r\n<p>The teams are&nbsp;Al Ahly SC and&nbsp;Zamalek SC, and they are both playing at Cairo International Stadium. The derby is known as the&nbsp;Clasico El-Arab.</p>\r\n<div><img style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/mohamed-salah.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" srcset=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/mohamed-salah-200x136.jpg 200w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/mohamed-salah-300x204.jpg 300w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/mohamed-salah-400x272.jpg 400w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/mohamed-salah-600x408.jpg 600w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/mohamed-salah.jpg 750w\" alt=\"mohamed salah\" width=\"750\" height=\"510\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/mohamed-salah.jpg\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/mohamed-salah-200x136.jpg 200w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/mohamed-salah-300x204.jpg 300w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/mohamed-salah-400x272.jpg 400w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/mohamed-salah-600x408.jpg 600w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/mohamed-salah.jpg 750w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" data-was-processed=\"true\" />\r\n<p>Photo: Alizada Studios / Shutterstock.com</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>7. EVERY CITY HAD THEIR FAVORITE GOD DURING ANCIENT TIMES</h2>\r\n<p>The Ancient Egyptians had so many gods that literally every city had their own favorite deity.</p>\r\n<h2>8. EGYPT IS HOME TO ONE OF THE WORLD&rsquo;S LARGEST DAM</h2>\r\n<p>Aswan high dam is the world&rsquo;s largest dam, built to contain the raging waters of the world&rsquo;s longest river, the Nile.</p>\r\n<div><img style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/aswan-high-dam.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" srcset=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/aswan-high-dam-200x133.jpg 200w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/aswan-high-dam-300x199.jpg 300w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/aswan-high-dam-400x265.jpg 400w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/aswan-high-dam-600x398.jpg 600w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/aswan-high-dam.jpg 750w\" alt=\"aswan high dam\" width=\"750\" height=\"497\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/aswan-high-dam.jpg\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/aswan-high-dam-200x133.jpg 200w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/aswan-high-dam-300x199.jpg 300w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/aswan-high-dam-400x265.jpg 400w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/aswan-high-dam-600x398.jpg 600w, https://www.swedishnomad.com/wp-content/images/2017/04/aswan-high-dam.jpg 750w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" data-was-processed=\"true\" />\r\n<p>Photo: Shutterstock</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>9. THE OFFICIAL LANGUAGE IS ARABIC</h2>\r\n<p>But, many also understand English or French. Egypt is also home to the largest Arabic population, another interesting fact about Egypt.</p>\r\n<h2>10. EGYPT HAS MORE THAN 3451 HOURS OF SUN EACH YEAR</h2>\r\n<p>Aswan&nbsp;is the third sunniest place in the world with 3863 hours of sun each year, that&rsquo;s 10 hours of sun a day!</p>\r\n<div>READ MORE:&nbsp;&nbsp;15 Reasons to Visit Egypt</div>\r\n<p>So,&nbsp;if you&rsquo;re longing for some extra sun, you should go to Aswan, in the southern part of the country!</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Do you know some more interesting facts about Egypt? Leave a comment and share your knowledge!&nbsp;</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', 'History', 'img/posts/post5baf7217ca3bc.jpg', 1, 'published', '2018-09-29 12:32:18.578745'),
(8, 'latest tecnologies', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h1>What are the latest technologies in IT industry?</h1>\r\n<p>Some future&nbsp;<a href=\"https://appinventiv.com/blog/10-tech-trends-that-will-become-mainstream-by-2020\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" data-qt-tooltip=\"appinventiv.com\" data-tooltip=\"attached\">technologies trends</a>&nbsp;that will rule the planet <a href=\"are:-\">are:-</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>1. AI</strong></p>\r\n<p>Artificial Intelligence has been continuing to make its place in the list of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://appinventiv.com/blog/complete-guide-biggest-tech-trends-2017\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" data-qt-tooltip=\"appinventiv.com\" data-tooltip=\"attached\">top technology trends</a>&nbsp;since quite some years. Its present day tasks of enabling computers to read (studying messages and reports), see (through facial recognition), listen (by enabling Amazon Echo to answer your command), speak ( Siri being able to give you an answer) and even record emotions (through affective computing) will help AI become a technology that no longer needs human intervention to aid its learning.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><canvas width=\"602.0\" height=\"349.86823529411765\"></canvas><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://qph.fs.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-67ebd298df90ad5644463b6abc3420d8\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>2. Voice</strong></p>\r\n<p>The future belongs to Voice. Google recently revealed that 20% of the searches on its mobile app and Android services are made by voice, and this number is going to increase in the next few years. The marketers also announced that search by voice will replace keyboards by 2022.</p>\r\n<p>Alexa,<a href=\"https://appinventiv.com/blog/best-new-features-google-assistant\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" data-qt-tooltip=\"appinventiv.com\">&nbsp;Google assistant</a>&nbsp;and Siri have already acquainted us with the power of voice in conducting everyday tasks, the applications have still remained very limited. Here&rsquo;s a demo video describing the future of Voice technology.</p>\r\n<div data-video-provider=\"youtube\" data-embed=\"&lt;iframe width=\">\" data-yt-id=\"D5VN56jQMWM\"&gt;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><strong>3. NLP</strong></p>\r\n<p>The majority of the businesses employing them to redefine their customer engagement policies. However, by 2020 chatbots would reach a whole different level with the integration of NLP.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><canvas width=\"602.0\" height=\"349.86823529411765\"></canvas><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://qph.fs.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-dfcd1e48d1e526bf4a809681c4ef6f8d\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>4. Blockchain</strong></p>\r\n<p>The rate at which Blockchain is growing has placed it at a pivotal point in the list of top technology trends 2020.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://appinventiv.com/blog/blockchain-technology-revolutionizing-mobile-app-security\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" data-qt-tooltip=\"appinventiv.com\">Blockchain technology</a>&nbsp;is definitely here to stay. While prevalent in only a handful of industries right now, by 2020 the world will see its mass adoption.</p>\r\n<p>Watch the video to know about B<a href=\"lockchain:-\">lockchain:-</a></p>\r\n<div data-video-provider=\"youtube\" data-embed=\"&lt;iframe width=\">\" data-yt-id=\"SSo_EIwHSd4\"&gt;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><strong>5. IoT</strong></p>\r\n<p>IoT has been finding itself in the list of up and coming technologies to look out for. Pretty much everything would be made smart in the coming time. There are already a lot of devices, but the IoT is only getting started. IHS has predicted there&rsquo;ll be over 75 billion total connected devices by 2020.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><canvas width=\"602.0\" height=\"349.86823529411765\"></canvas><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://qph.fs.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-e43dcb0f91dfff43ac9ec69e813b1abf\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>6. Edge Computing</strong></p>\r\n<p>Edge computing is a computing element where everything from &ndash; information processing, content collection, and its delivery are situated close to the source of information. Latency and connectivity challenges, bandwidth restrictions, and higher functionality are some of the benefits that get embedded at the edge of the source.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><canvas width=\"602.0\" height=\"349.86823529411765\"></canvas><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://qph.fs.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-7027bb3eedc3df424d704134f44793f8\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>7. Prescriptive Analysis</strong></p>\r\n<p>While the present time is that of predictive analysis, with software giving out prompts on the basis of users&rsquo; behaviour and past interaction, in the coming time, the plethora of collected user data will help businesses in a much different way.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><canvas width=\"602.0\" height=\"349.86823529411765\"></canvas><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://qph.fs.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-7e1189ddedfd105d37d0a8f42a82faca\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>8. 5G</strong></p>\r\n<p>5g will find its place in the market very soon, bringing with itself benefits such as high internet speed, lower latency, and higher capacities. The benefits that will make it a prime technology trend in 2020 and beyond.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><canvas width=\"602.0\" height=\"349.86823529411765\"></canvas><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://qph.fs.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-454d6cd5a9c48d27b9b29e36d53c3043\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>9. Facial Recognition</strong></p>\r\n<p>Your face will become the ideal technology partner by 2020. What started with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://appinventiv.com/blog/apple-iphone-x-different-gestures\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" data-qt-tooltip=\"appinventiv.com\">iPhone X with its face ID</a>&nbsp;will be taken ahead by a number of industries who would now be using your face for a series of different applications.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><canvas width=\"602.0\" height=\"349.86823529411765\"></canvas><img style=\"max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://qph.fs.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-609161eb99dcf712d527724f88fa2f7d\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>10. Automation</strong></p>\r\n<p>From packaging juice boxes to delivering pizza in self driving vehicles, automation is fast climbing the food chain from doing routine tasks to a lot more complex, decision making tasks.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', 'technology', 'img/posts/post5baf746b4e398.jpg', 1, 'published', '2018-09-29 12:46:21.854977');
