INSERT INTO `posts` (`post_id`, `title`, `post`, `category_id`, `image`, `author_id`, `status`, `post_date`) VALUES
(11, ' Inspirational Short Stories', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">15 Best Inspirational Short Stories that Will Motivate You</h1>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"View all posts in Uncategorized\" href=\"https://www.livin3.com/category/uncategorized\">UNCATEGORIZED</a><a href=\"https://www.livin3.com/5-motivational-and-inspiring-short-stories#comments\">238 COMMENTS</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; width: 750px;\" src=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/people-holding-sign.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 668px) 100vw, 668px\" srcset=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/people-holding-sign.jpg 668w, https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/people-holding-sign-300x198.jpg 300w, https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/people-holding-sign-100x65.jpg 100w\" alt=\"\" width=\"668\" height=\"441\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<section>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Everyone gets a little down in the dumps sometimes. Rather than searching the internet for cat pictures or drowning your sorrows in junk, check out these motivational short stories. We have put together the best inspirational short stories, both real and fictional, to pull you from your slump, make you smile and inspire you.</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><center>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</center></div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The Best 5 Inspirational Short Stories About Life</strong><strong><br /></strong></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">When life has got you in a slump, turn to these motivational short stories. Not only is reading them like getting an internet hug for the soul, but they just may spark an idea or a change in you for the better. Read on and get ready to smile.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>1. Everyone Has a Story in Life</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A 24 year old boy seeing out from the train&rsquo;s window shouted&hellip;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;Dad, look the trees are going behind!&rdquo;</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Dad smiled and a young couple sitting nearby, looked at the 24 year old&rsquo;s childish behavior with pity, suddenly he again exclaimed&hellip;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;Dad, look the clouds are running with us!&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The couple couldn&rsquo;t resist and said to the old man&hellip;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><center>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</center></div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;Why don&rsquo;t you take your son to a good doctor?&rdquo; The old man smiled and said&hellip;&ldquo;I did and we are just coming from the hospital, my son was blind from birth, he just got his eyes today.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Every single person on the planet has a story. Don&rsquo;t judge people before you truly know them. The truth might surprise you.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>2. Shake off Your Problems</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A man&rsquo;s favorite donkey falls into a deep precipice. He can&rsquo;t pull it out no matter how hard he tries. He therefore decides to bury it alive.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Soil is poured onto the donkey from above. The donkey feels the load, shakes it off, and steps on it. More soil is poured.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">It shakes it off and steps up. The more the load was poured, the higher it rose. By noon, the donkey was grazing in green pastures.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">After much shaking off (of problems) And stepping up (learning from them), One will graze in GREEN PASTURES.</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>Related:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.livin3.com/positive-quotes\">127 Positive Quotes to Help You Live Your Best Life</a></strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>3. The Elephant Rope</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/elephant-and-rope.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4691\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 50%; line-height: 0;\" src=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/elephant-and-rope.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px\" srcset=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/elephant-and-rope.jpg 480w, https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/elephant-and-rope-300x221.jpg 300w\" alt=\"\" width=\"480\" height=\"354\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">As a man was passing the elephants, he suddenly stopped, confused by the fact that these huge creatures were being held by only a small rope tied to their front leg. No chains, no cages. It was obvious that the elephants could, at anytime, break away from their bonds but for some reason, they did not.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">He saw a trainer nearby and asked why these animals just stood there and made no attempt to get away. &ldquo;Well,&rdquo; trainer said, &ldquo;when they are very young and much smaller we use the same size rope to tie them and, at that age, it&rsquo;s enough to hold them. As they grow up, they are conditioned to believe they cannot break away. They believe the rope can still hold them, so they never try to break free.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The man was amazed. These animals could at any time break free from their bonds but because they believed they couldn&rsquo;t, they were stuck right where they were.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Like the elephants, how many of us go through life hanging onto a belief that we cannot do something, simply because we failed at it once before?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Failure is part of learning; we should never give up the struggle in life.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>4. Potatoes, Eggs, and Coffee Beans</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Once upon a time a daughter complained to her father that her life was miserable and that she didn&rsquo;t know how she was going to make it. She was tired of fighting and struggling all the time. It seemed just as one problem was solved, another one soon followed.</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><center>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</center></div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Her father, a chef, took her to the kitchen. He filled three pots with water and placed each on a high fire. Once the three pots began to boil, he placed potatoes in one pot, eggs in the second pot, and ground coffee beans in the third pot.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">He then let them sit and boil, without saying a word to his daughter. The daughter, moaned and impatiently waited, wondering what he was doing.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">After twenty minutes he turned off the burners. He took the potatoes out of the pot and placed them in a bowl. He pulled the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.livin3.com/boiled-egg-diet\">boiled eggs</a>&nbsp;out and placed them in a bowl.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">He then ladled the coffee out and placed it in a cup. Turning to her he asked. &ldquo;Daughter, what do you see?&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;Potatoes, eggs, and coffee,&rdquo; she hastily replied.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;Look closer,&rdquo; he said, &ldquo;and touch the potatoes.&rdquo; She did and noted that they were soft. He then asked her to take an egg and break it. After pulling off the shell, she observed the hard-boiled egg. Finally, he asked her to sip the coffee. Its rich aroma brought a smile to her face.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;Father, what does this mean?&rdquo; she asked.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">He then explained that the potatoes, the eggs and coffee beans had each faced the same adversity&ndash; the boiling water.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">However, each one reacted differently.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The potato went in strong, hard, and unrelenting, but in boiling water, it became soft and weak.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The egg was fragile, with the thin outer shell protecting its liquid interior until it was put in the boiling water. Then the inside of the egg became hard.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">However, the ground coffee beans were unique. After they were exposed to the boiling water, they changed the water and created something new.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;Which are you,&rdquo; he asked his daughter. &ldquo;When adversity knocks on your door, how do you respond? Are you a potato, an egg, or a coffee bean? &ldquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"Moral:In\">Moral:In</a> life, things happen around us, things happen to us, but the only thing that truly matters is what happens within us.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Which one are you?</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><center>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</center></div>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>5. A Dish of Ice Cream</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/dish-of-ice-cream.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4692\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 50%; line-height: 0;\" src=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/dish-of-ice-cream.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 287px) 100vw, 287px\" srcset=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/dish-of-ice-cream.jpg 287w, https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/dish-of-ice-cream-125x125.jpg 125w\" alt=\"\" width=\"287\" height=\"290\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">In the days when an ice cream sundae cost much less, a 10 year old boy entered a hotel coffee shop and sat at a table. A waitress put a glass of water in front of him.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;How much is an ice cream sundae?&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;50 cents,&rdquo; replied the waitress.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The little boy pulled his hand out of his pocket and studied a number of coins in it.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;How much is a dish of plain ice cream?&rdquo; he inquired. Some people were now waiting for a table and the waitress was a bit impatient.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;35 cents,&rdquo; she said brusquely.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The little boy again counted the coins. &ldquo;I&rsquo;ll have the plain ice cream,&rdquo; he said.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The waitress brought the ice cream, put the bill on the table and walked away. The boy finished the ice cream, paid the cashier and departed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">When the waitress came back, she began wiping down the table and then swallowed hard at what she saw.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There, placed neatly beside the empty dish, were 15 cents &ndash; her tip.</p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Motivational Stories for Business and Work</strong></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Succeeding in business is no easy feat. It&rsquo;s too easy to let business knock you down. Instead of throwing in the towel when there is a business problem, pick yourself back up, buckle down, and get to work. These motivational stories prove that with a little hard work, any amount of business success is possible.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>1. Colonel Sanders | Kentucky Fried Chicken</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/KFC-owner.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4688\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; line-height: 0;\" src=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/KFC-owner.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"699\" height=\"507\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Once, there was an older man, who was broke, living in a tiny house and owned a beat up car. He was living off of $99 social security checks. At 65 years of age, he decide things had to change. So he thought about what he had to offer. His friends raved about his chicken recipe. He decided that this was his best shot at making a change.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">He left Kentucky and traveled to different states to try to sell his recipe. He told restaurant owners that he had a mouthwatering chicken recipe. He offered the recipe to them for free, just asking for a small percentage on the items sold. Sounds like a good deal, right?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Unfortunately, not to most of the restaurants. He heard NO over 1000 times. Even after all of those rejections, he didn&rsquo;t give up. He believed his chicken recipe was something special. He got rejected 1009 times before he heard his first yes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">With that one success Colonel Hartland Sanders changed the way Americans eat chicken. Kentucky Fried Chicken, popularly known as KFC, was born.</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><center>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</center></div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Remember, never give up and always believe in yourself in spite of rejection.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>2. The Obstacle in our Path</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There once was a very wealthy and curious king. This king had a huge boulder placed in the middle of a road. Then he hid nearby to see if anyone would try to remove the gigantic rock from the road.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The first people to pass by were some of the king&rsquo;s wealthiest merchants and courtiers. Rather than moving it, they simply walked around it. A few loudly blamed the King for not maintaining the roads. Not one of them tried to move the boulder.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Finally, a peasant came along. His arms were full of vegetables. When he got near the boulder, rather than simply walking around it as the others had, the peasant put down his load and tried to move the stone to the side of the road. It took a lot of effort but he finally succeeded.</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The peasant gathered up his load and was ready to go on his way when he say a purse lying in the road where the boulder had been. The peasant opened the purse. The purse was stuffed full of gold coins and a note from the king. The king&rsquo;s note said the purse&rsquo;s gold was a reward for moving the boulder from the road.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The king showed the peasant what many of us never understand: every obstacle presents an opportunity to improve our condition.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>3. Value</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/20-dollar-bill.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4696\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 50%; line-height: 0;\" src=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/20-dollar-bill.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 314px) 100vw, 314px\" srcset=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/20-dollar-bill.jpg 339w, https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/20-dollar-bill-257x300.jpg 257w\" alt=\"\" width=\"314\" height=\"366\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A popular speaker started off a seminar by holding up a $20 bill. A crowd of 200 had gathered to hear him speak. He asked, &ldquo;Who would like this $20 bill?&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">200 hands went up.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">He said, &ldquo;I am going to give this $20 to one of you but first, let me do this.&rdquo; He crumpled the bill up.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">He then asked, &ldquo;Who still wants it?&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All 200 hands were still raised.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;Well,&rdquo; he replied, &ldquo;What if I do this?&rdquo; Then he dropped the bill on the ground and stomped on it with his shoes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">He picked it up, and showed it to the crowd. The bill was all crumpled and dirty.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;Now who still wants it?&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">All the hands still went up.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&ldquo;My friends, I have just showed you a very important lesson. No matter what I did to the money, you still wanted it because it did not decrease in value. It was still worth $20. Many times in our lives, life crumples us and grinds us into the dirt. We make bad decisions or deal with poor circumstances. We feel worthless. But no matter what has happened or what will happen, you will never lose your value. You are special &ndash; Don&rsquo;t ever forget it!</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>4. A Very Special Bank Account</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Imagine you had a bank account that deposited $86,400 each morning. The account carries over no balance from day to day, allows you to keep no cash balance, and every evening cancels whatever part of the amount you had failed to use during the day. What would you do? Draw out every dollar each day!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">We all have such a bank. Its name is Time. Every morning, it credits you with 86,400 seconds. Every night it writes off, as lost, whatever time you have failed to use wisely. It carries over no balance from day to day. It allows no overdraft so you can&rsquo;t borrow against yourself or use more time than you have. Each day, the account starts fresh. Each night, it destroys an unused time. If you fail to use the day&rsquo;s deposits, it&rsquo;s your loss and you can&rsquo;t appeal to get it back.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There is never any borrowing time. You can&rsquo;t take a loan out on your time or against someone else&rsquo;s. The time you have is the time you have and that is that. Time management is yours to decide how you spend the time, just as with money you decide how you spend the money. It is never the case of us not having enough time to do things, but the case of whether we want to do them and where they fall in our priorities.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Motivational Weight Loss Stories</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Losing weight feels like a constant uphill battle. Shedding stubborn pounds and getting healthy can be a lot of hard work. During a plateau or at the beginning of the a weight loss journey, it&rsquo;s easy to be discouraged. Find ways to motivate yourself, like reading these inspirational weight loss stories. Know if they can do it, so can you!</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>1. Unstoppable<br /></strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Sara-Murphy1-630x472.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4687\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%; line-height: 0;\" src=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Sara-Murphy1-630x472.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" srcset=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Sara-Murphy1-630x472.jpg 630w, https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Sara-Murphy1-630x472-300x225.jpg 300w\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"472\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://heidipowell.net/8658/extreme-weight-loss-our-marathon-runner-sara/\">Extreme Makeover</a>&nbsp;features a celebrity trainer helping very overweight individuals reach their weight loss goals. Sometimes, their attitudes aren&rsquo;t great, but other times, the people on the show are truly amazing, like Sara. Sara is a little person, standing at only 4&rsquo;5&Prime;. She was a nutrition speaker on local television shows at the start of her journey, but ashamed of herself. Not only had she spent her life dealing with her short stature, but she had suffered greatly at the hands of her sister. She turned to eating and by the time she was 37 years old, weighed over 200 pounds.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sara-before-after-lr.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4686\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 50%; line-height: 0;\" src=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sara-before-after-lr.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" srcset=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sara-before-after-lr.jpg 600w, https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sara-before-after-lr-300x232.jpg 300w\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"464\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">When she began her time on Extreme Makeover, her first challenge was to climb the stairs of an amphitheater holding an 80 pound weight. The stairs came up past her knees. But she didn&rsquo;t complain once. She kept going. Slowly, all the people in the theater started to watch her. By the time she reached the last step, the crowd cheered for her.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Her trainer gave her the goal to run a half marathon 6 months after starting her diet and exercise program. Sara said no. She wouldn&rsquo;t run the half. Instead she would run a full marathon. Her trainer advised against it because it would be extra hard on her body. She&rsquo;d have to take many extra strides due to her short stature. Sara didn&rsquo;t care. She ran the whole marathon.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">She succeeded in loosing more than half her body weight and becoming a runner, like she had always dreamed.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>2. Winning the Battle</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Adrienne Brown shared her weight loss journey with&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.goodhousekeeping.com/health/diet-nutrition/g1298/weight-loss-stories/?slide=2\">Good Housekeeping</a>. Adrienne loved to eat and was a bit food obsessed. As an adult, she owned two refrigerators stocked with food. She was already overweight at 180 pounds when her weight shot up as she battled breast cancer.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Adrienne got serious about her health during her battle with cancer. Inspired by Jennifer Garner in&nbsp;<em>Alias</em>&nbsp;and determined to be healthier, Adrienne lost 90 pounds in a year by eliminating processed foods and exercising. She made it manageable by breaking her goal into 10 pound increments and keeping a positive attitude.</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>Related:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.livin3.com/garcinia-cambogia-and-apple-cider-vinegar-diet\">Garcinia Cambogia and Apple Cider Vinegar: Is it Worth It?</a></strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>3. The Weight Was Wrong</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Drew Carey has spent much of his career in the spotlight. Fans of the comedic actor remember him as the overweight star of the&nbsp;<em>Drew Carey Show</em>. He shocked his following by appearing on his new job as the host of the&nbsp;<em>The Price is Right</em>, a full 80 pounds lighter. There was no magic trick to his weight loss. Carey lost weight the old fashioned way, by counting calories and logging 45 minute cardio sessions on the treadmill.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Remember, you don&rsquo;t have to try the newest fad (<a href=\"http://www.livin3.com/the-3-day-military-diet\">The 3 Day Military Diet</a>). Find what works for you and just stick with it. Little by little you will reach your goals.</p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Funny Motivational Stories</strong></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">These funny motivational stories will give your attitude a little nudge in the right direction. They are also guaranteed to put a smile on your face and may even make you chuckle.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>1. The Dean Schooled Them<br /></strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sitting-student-at-desk.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-4690\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 50%; line-height: 0;\" src=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sitting-student-at-desk.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 356px) 100vw, 356px\" srcset=\"https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sitting-student-at-desk.jpg 418w, https://www.livin3.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sitting-student-at-desk-237x300.jpg 237w\" alt=\"\" width=\"356\" height=\"451\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">One night four college kids stayed out late, partying and having a good time. They paid no mind to the test they had scheduled for the next day and didn&rsquo;t study. In the morning, they hatched a plan to get out of taking their test. They covered themselves with grease and dirt and went to the Dean&rsquo;s office. Once there, they said they had been to a wedding the previous night and on the way back they got a flat tire and had to push the car back to campus.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The Dean listened to their tale of woe and thought. He offered them a retest three days later. They thanked him and accepted his offer.hat time.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">When the test day arrived, they went to the Dean. The Dean put them all in separate rooms for the test. They were fine with this since they had all studied hard. Then they saw the test. It had 2 questions.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">1) Your Name __________ (1 Points)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">2) Which tire burst? __________ (99 Points)<br />Options &ndash; (a) Front Left (b) Front Right (c) Back Left (d) Back Right</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><em>The lesson:</em></strong>&nbsp;always be responsible and make wise decisions.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>2. The Right Place</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A mother and a baby camel were lying around under a tree.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Then the baby camel asked, &ldquo;Why do camels have humps?&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The mother camel considered this and said, &ldquo;We are desert animals so we have the humps to store water so we can survive with very little water.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The baby camel thought for a moment then said, &ldquo;Ok&hellip;why are our legs long and our feet rounded?&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The mama replied, &ldquo;They are meant for walking in the desert.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The baby paused. After a beat, the camel asked, &ldquo;Why are our eyelashes long? Sometimes they get in my way.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The mama responded, &ldquo;Those long thick eyelashes protect your eyes from the desert sand when it blows in the wind.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The baby thought and thought. Then he said, &ldquo;I see. So the hump is to store water when we are in the desert, the legs are for walking through the desert and these eye lashes protect my eyes from the desert then why in the Zoo?&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>The Lesson:</strong></em>&nbsp;Skills and abilities are only useful if you are in the right place at the right time. Otherwise they go to waste.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>3. On God&rsquo;s Time</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A man walked to the top of a hill to talk to God.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The man asked, &ldquo;God, what&rsquo;s a million years to you?&rdquo; and God said, &ldquo;A minute.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Then the man asked, &ldquo;Well, what&rsquo;s a million dollars to you?&rdquo; and God said, &ldquo;A penny.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Then the man asked, &ldquo;God&hellip;..can I have a penny?&rdquo; and God said, &ldquo;Sure&hellip;..in a minute.&rdquo;</p>\r\n</section>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', 'Motivations', 'img/posts/post5baf79c244042.jpg', 1, 'published', '2018-09-29 13:10:26.280594');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`post_id`, `title`, `post`, `category_id`, `image`, `author_id`, `status`, `post_date`) VALUES
(12, 'Best Inspirational Movies', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<div>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">20+ Best Inspirational Movies Based On True Stories</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Some characters are always hidden in layers of history. But movie makers always try and help us in celebrating such success and inspiring stories which we may have ignored or never even heard about. So here&rsquo;s a list of 20+ best inspirational and motivational movies&nbsp;<a href=\"https://moviesdrop.com/info/true-stories/\">based on true stories</a>&nbsp;which may help you in introducing to the world&rsquo;s most inspiring people, who broke all shackles and lived on their terms, people who never gave up and were pure genius.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Inspirational Movies Based On True Stories &amp; Events</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">1. Schindler&rsquo;s List (1993)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Schindlers-List.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 634px) 100vw, 634px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Schindlers-List.jpg 634w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Schindlers-List-300x218.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Schindlers-List-247x180.jpg 247w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Schindlers-List-102x75.jpg 102w\" alt=\"Schindler\'s List\" width=\"634\" height=\"462\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The year 1939, World War II. A German political man wants to profit from the war but needs workers in his factory. What does he do? He hires Jews who are being exterminated under Hitler&rsquo;s rule. He employs about 300 of them to work in his factory with proper labor arrangements. But gradually realizes, he&rsquo;s giving them a new life also. He goes through a list of measures to keep his workers safe, so as to maintain the factory running, which in turn also saves Jews from the SS.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">2. Saving Private Ryan (1998)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Saving-Private-Ryan.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 852px) 100vw, 852px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Saving-Private-Ryan.jpg 852w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Saving-Private-Ryan-300x169.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Saving-Private-Ryan-768x433.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Saving-Private-Ryan-320x180.jpg 320w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Saving-Private-Ryan-600x338.jpg 600w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Saving-Private-Ryan-200x113.jpg 200w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Saving-Private-Ryan-195x110.jpg 195w\" alt=\"Saving Private Ryan\" width=\"852\" height=\"480\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A movie inspired by the invasion of Normandy in World War II. A battalion of soldiers set out to search for their fallen comrade, Private Ryan, who has lost his three brothers in the war. With enemies on their back and their desperation to save Ryan, each soldier goes through a state of Nirvana where they meet their self. Each one of them discovers their strength to overcome fears of uncertain future.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">3. Patch Adams (1998)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Patch-Adams-1998-1024x576.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Patch-Adams-1998-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Patch-Adams-1998-300x169.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Patch-Adams-1998-768x432.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Patch-Adams-1998-320x180.jpg 320w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Patch-Adams-1998-600x338.jpg 600w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Patch-Adams-1998-200x113.jpg 200w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Patch-Adams-1998-195x110.jpg 195w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Patch-Adams-1998.jpg 1420w\" alt=\"Patch Adams (1998)\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A hunter named Peter Adams suffers from manic depression at a mental hospital. After a long struggle, he decides he wants to open his medical clinic. He gets admission into Virginia Medical University but doesn&rsquo;t agree with the patient care methods. Along with a wealthy friend who is ready to invest in his practice, he opens his clinic for those who do not have medical insurance. But a tragic accident makes him realize that the path is not easy.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">4. October Sky (1999)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/October-Sky-1999-1024x576.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/October-Sky-1999-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/October-Sky-1999-300x169.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/October-Sky-1999-768x432.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/October-Sky-1999-320x180.jpg 320w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/October-Sky-1999-600x338.jpg 600w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/October-Sky-1999-200x113.jpg 200w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/October-Sky-1999-195x110.jpg 195w\" alt=\"October Sky (1999)\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A simple coal miner from West Virginia, John Hickam wants his sons to follow his footsteps, but unexpectedly both turn out to be pretty smart. Jim enrolls into a football scholarship, and Homer becomes interested in rocket science after seeing Sputnik 1. John disapproves of Homer;s hobby, but Homer starts building rockets with the help of his friends and a Teach Laura Dern, who can provide him with a better life.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">5. A Beautiful Mind (2001)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/A-Beautiful-Mind-2001-1024x572.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/A-Beautiful-Mind-2001-1024x572.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/A-Beautiful-Mind-2001-300x169.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/A-Beautiful-Mind-2001-768x429.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/A-Beautiful-Mind-2001-320x180.jpg 320w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/A-Beautiful-Mind-2001-200x113.jpg 200w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/A-Beautiful-Mind-2001.jpg 1336w\" alt=\"A Beautiful Mind (2001)\" width=\"640\" height=\"358\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Remember Nash equilibrium from Graduate level Mathematics? Many of us might have forgotten it. A beautiful Mind is the real life story of John Forbes Nash Jr mixed with the biography written by the same name by Sylvia Nasar. From heights of success to dungeons of failure, John faced it all in his life. He made an amazing discovery pretty early in his life and was about to be internationally recognized. But suddenly he gets on a path which takes him on a self-discovery journey, which is painful and scary.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">6. Catch Me If You Can (2002)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Catch-Me-If-You-Can-2002.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Catch-Me-If-You-Can-2002.jpg 800w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Catch-Me-If-You-Can-2002-300x172.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Catch-Me-If-You-Can-2002-768x441.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Catch-Me-If-You-Can-2002-314x180.jpg 314w\" alt=\"Catch Me If You Can (2002)\" width=\"800\" height=\"459\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">As kids, we wanted to be a lot of things. Surgeon, Pilot, writer, astronaut, Policeman, etc. There was one guy in history who was many of these things, even before his 18th Birthday! Frank Abagnale was a master forger, and deception was in his blood. He became the most successful bank robber in the history of U.S. Enters FBI Agent Carl Hanratty, who makes the capture of Frank his life mission. But the only problem is, Frank is always one step ahead of Carl.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">7. Hotel Rwanda (2004)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Hotel-Rwanda-2004-1024x576.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Hotel-Rwanda-2004-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Hotel-Rwanda-2004-300x169.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Hotel-Rwanda-2004-768x432.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Hotel-Rwanda-2004-320x180.jpg 320w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Hotel-Rwanda-2004-600x338.jpg 600w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Hotel-Rwanda-2004-200x113.jpg 200w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Hotel-Rwanda-2004-195x110.jpg 195w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Hotel-Rwanda-2004.jpg 1280w\" alt=\"Hotel Rwanda (2004)\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A true story based on Rwanda Genocide, Paul Rusesabagina manages a hotel based in Hutu and lives a regular with wife and three children. Life takes a turn when Hutu military forces take up the task of the cleansing Tutsi minority. After looking at the genocide happening in front of eyes, Paul allows refugees for camping in his hotel, saving as many as he can. But problems increase when UN pulls out from the area, and he is left all alone to face the blazing fire of Hutu military forces.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">8. The Aviator (2004)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Aviator-2004-1024x576.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Aviator-2004-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Aviator-2004-300x169.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Aviator-2004-768x432.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Aviator-2004-320x180.jpg 320w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Aviator-2004-600x338.jpg 600w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Aviator-2004-200x113.jpg 200w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Aviator-2004-195x110.jpg 195w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Aviator-2004.jpg 1600w\" alt=\"The Aviator (2004)\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Some successful people suffer from a lot of things, stress being one of the main culprits. Aviator is a story about one of those people only. Billionaire Howard Hughes has everything, from big budget Hollywood films to leading ladies as his lover and he is an aviation pioneer too. But when he is not all of this, he is a person who is tormented and suffers from phobias and depression. The more successful he gets, the more he is plunging into darkness.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">9. Coach Carter (2005)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Coach-Carter-2005-1024x680.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Coach-Carter-2005-1024x680.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Coach-Carter-2005-300x199.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Coach-Carter-2005-768x510.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Coach-Carter-2005-271x180.jpg 271w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Coach-Carter-2005-84x55.jpg 84w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Coach-Carter-2005.jpg 1200w\" alt=\"Coach Carter (2005)\" width=\"640\" height=\"425\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Studies and recreation should go hand in hand; we have been listening to this since we were kids. Coach Carter is the story of Ken Carter, who returns to his old high school in Richmond to coach the basketball, team. He succeeds in this, but then player&rsquo;s academic grades start to fall. After receiving a backlash from parents and authorities, he shuts himself up and withdraws participation from the championship season, determined that the players should excel in court as well as in classes.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">10. The World&rsquo;s Fastest Indian (2005)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-World%E2%80%99s-Fastest-Indian-2005-1024x681.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-World&rsquo;s-Fastest-Indian-2005-1024x681.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-World&rsquo;s-Fastest-Indian-2005-300x200.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-World&rsquo;s-Fastest-Indian-2005-768x511.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-World&rsquo;s-Fastest-Indian-2005-271x180.jpg 271w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-World&rsquo;s-Fastest-Indian-2005-84x55.jpg 84w\" alt=\"The World&rsquo;s Fastest Indian (2005)\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A biker;s delight, The World&rsquo;s Fastest Indian is based on the true story of Burth Munro from New Zealand, who perfects his mean machine to take it to Utah and set a world record for fastest speed in salt flats. Astonishingly, the world record that was set by Munro in the year 1967 has still not been broken by anyone!</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">11. Rescue Dawn (2006)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Rescue-Dawn.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 791px) 100vw, 791px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Rescue-Dawn.jpg 791w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Rescue-Dawn-300x189.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Rescue-Dawn-768x485.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Rescue-Dawn-285x180.jpg 285w\" alt=\"Rescue Dawn (2006)\" width=\"791\" height=\"500\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A true story based on Vietnam war, Dieter Dengler is injured and captured by enemy soldiers in Laos. Now based in a POW (Prisoner of War) camp, Dengler and his mates go through hunger, torture, and sickness while they await their chance to be rescued or escape.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">12. Pursuit of Happyness (2006)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Pursuit-of-Happyness-2006-1024x683.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Pursuit-of-Happyness-2006-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Pursuit-of-Happyness-2006-300x200.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Pursuit-of-Happyness-2006-768x512.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Pursuit-of-Happyness-2006-270x180.jpg 270w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Pursuit-of-Happyness-2006-84x55.jpg 84w\" alt=\"Pursuit of Happyness (2006)\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">One of the most emotional films of all times, Chris Gardner, recently divorced and a single father without a job has to take care of his kid. Thrown out of their apartment, now they have nowhere to go and seek residence in shelters where you have to get in line to get bread and bed. Even after landing an internship at a prestigious brokerage firm, they hardly have enough money. But Chris never bows to despair and keeps on working hard for his son to create a better life. Grab some tissues when you sit down to watch this one!</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">13. Glory Road (2006)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/The-Glory-Road-2006-1024x587.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/The-Glory-Road-2006-1024x587.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/The-Glory-Road-2006-300x172.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/The-Glory-Road-2006-768x440.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/The-Glory-Road-2006-314x180.jpg 314w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/The-Glory-Road-2006.jpg 1387w\" alt=\"The Glory Road (2006)\" width=\"640\" height=\"367\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The year 1966, when racism was still prevailing in many areas of USA. Texas Miners, a football team, gets a new coach, Don Haskiins, who believes in pure talent over race. The town is in an uproar with gossip, but their mouths simply shut when they see that the team is doing great on the field. But when black players Bobby Joe Hill and captain Harry Flournoy being to dominate other teammates, the future is in jeopardy.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">14. Freedom Writers (2007)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Freedom-Writers-2007-1024x578.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Freedom-Writers-2007-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Freedom-Writers-2007-300x169.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Freedom-Writers-2007-768x433.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Freedom-Writers-2007-320x180.jpg 320w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Freedom-Writers-2007-600x338.jpg 600w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Freedom-Writers-2007-200x113.jpg 200w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Freedom-Writers-2007-195x110.jpg 195w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Freedom-Writers-2007.jpg 1280w\" alt=\"Freedom Writers (2007)\" width=\"640\" height=\"361\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">How we underestimate writing journals every day. But a teacher in racially divided Los Angeles school made others realize how important it is to do that. Starring Hilary Swank, Freedom writers is the story about a teacher who inspires her students to prioritize their education by including material related to their lives, and she encourages them to keep journals to know more about themselves.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">15. Into the Wild (2007)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Into-the-Wild-2007.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Into-the-Wild-2007.jpg 600w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Into-the-Wild-2007-300x200.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Into-the-Wild-2007-270x180.jpg 270w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Into-the-Wild-2007-84x55.jpg 84w\" alt=\"Into the Wild (2007)\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">A movie for some people who are tired of mundane lives and simply existing to survive. Christopher McCandless, son of wealthy parents, gives up his college degree from Emory University and credentials of being a top student and athlete. To live close to himself. He gives away all his savings to charity and sets out the Alaskan wilderness, to be close to nature and not just survive, but to live.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">DO CHECK OUT:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://moviesdrop.com/2015/06/best-travel-movies-based-on-true-stories-3965/\">Best Travel Movies Based On True Stories</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">16. The Blind Side (2009)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/The-Blind-Side-2009-1024x684.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/The-Blind-Side-2009-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/The-Blind-Side-2009-300x201.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/The-Blind-Side-2009-768x513.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/The-Blind-Side-2009-269x180.jpg 269w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/The-Blind-Side-2009-84x55.jpg 84w\" alt=\"The Blind Side (2009)\" width=\"640\" height=\"428\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">An academy award winning movie, The Blind side shows how racial biases can put anyone;s morale down. And some people are true humans. Michael Oher is a black homeless teen who is taken in by a white family, Tuohy&rsquo;s. They become Michael;s legal guardians, providing him everything, from education to a home. With the help of his new found family, Michael then realizes his potential to be a good student and great footballers, breaking all racial biases chains.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">17. Invictus (2009)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Invictus-2009-1024x576.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Invictus-2009-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Invictus-2009-300x169.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Invictus-2009-768x432.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Invictus-2009-320x180.jpg 320w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Invictus-2009-600x338.jpg 600w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Invictus-2009-200x113.jpg 200w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Invictus-2009-195x110.jpg 195w\" alt=\"Invictus (2009)\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Based on a true incident from Nelson Mandela&rsquo;s life, as soon as apartheid was removed, recently elected President Nelson Mandela has a task to improve racially and economically divided South Africa. Believing in the power of sports, Mandela teams up with Francois Pienaar, who is the captain of a football team, to unite Soth Africans to play in the 1995 Football World Cup.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">18. Moneyball (2011)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Moneyball-2011-1024x550.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Moneyball-2011-1024x550.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Moneyball-2011-300x161.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Moneyball-2011-768x413.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Moneyball-2011-320x172.jpg 320w\" alt=\"Moneyball (2011)\" width=\"640\" height=\"344\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">How to convert weak into strong is what Moneyball is about. The coach of Oakland;s A, a baseball team feels that all the baseball wisdom is faulty. Faced with a tight budget when he wants to hire best pitchers, he plans to reinvent the team by hiring Peter Brand. They both set out to challenge old school probabilities which restrict bin players to become the best players, even after having the required talent.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">19. Intouchables (2011)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Intouchables-2011-1024x576.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Intouchables-2011-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Intouchables-2011-300x169.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Intouchables-2011-768x432.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Intouchables-2011-320x180.jpg 320w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Intouchables-2011-600x338.jpg 600w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Intouchables-2011-200x113.jpg 200w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Intouchables-2011-195x110.jpg 195w\" alt=\"Intouchables (2011)\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The world which judges people by race and color, a wealthy philanthropist, suffering from quadriplegic hires a recently released from Prison man, to work for him full time as his caretaker. An employment opportunity which turns into a beautiful and unlikely bond of friendship.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">20. Lincoln (2012)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Lincoln-2012-1024x682.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Lincoln-2012-1024x682.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Lincoln-2012-300x200.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Lincoln-2012-768x512.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Lincoln-2012-270x180.jpg 270w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Lincoln-2012-84x55.jpg 84w\" alt=\"Lincoln (2012)\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The most famous president in the American history, who took a stand for the abolition of slavery when Civil War tore America. He uses his humanity and political skills to push the people and government to aim towards a greater good for all humanity by abolishing slavery.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">21. Dallas Buyers Club (2013)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Dallas-Buyers-Club-2013-1024x766.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Dallas-Buyers-Club-2013-1024x766.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Dallas-Buyers-Club-2013-300x225.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Dallas-Buyers-Club-2013-768x575.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Dallas-Buyers-Club-2013-241x180.jpg 241w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Dallas-Buyers-Club-2013-102x75.jpg 102w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Dallas-Buyers-Club-2013-210x158.jpg 210w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Dallas-Buyers-Club-2013-390x293.jpg 390w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Dallas-Buyers-Club-2013-600x450.jpg 600w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Dallas-Buyers-Club-2013.jpg 1200w\" alt=\"Dallas Buyers Club (2013)\" width=\"640\" height=\"479\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The year 1980, Texas. An electrician, Ron Woodroof gets a shock when he gets to know that he has AIDS. With only 30 days to live, Ron doesn&rsquo;t give up on his life and starts seeing alternate therapies and smuggling of unapproved drugs. He teams up with fellow AIDS patient to sell drugs to people who have been failed by medical establishments.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">22. The Wolf of Wall Street (2013)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/The-Wolf-of-Wall-Street-2013.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 612px) 100vw, 612px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/The-Wolf-of-Wall-Street-2013.jpg 612w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/The-Wolf-of-Wall-Street-2013-300x155.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/The-Wolf-of-Wall-Street-2013-320x166.jpg 320w\" alt=\"The Wolf of Wall Street (2013)\" width=\"612\" height=\"318\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Another miss for Leonardo Di Caprio from Academy Awards. But this movie made people crazy! In the year 1987, Jordan Belfort takes up an entry level job at a brokerage firm to understand inside out of the profession. Then while still in his 20&rsquo;s, he opens a firm, Stratton Oakmont by teaming up with his friend. The company makes a huge profit by defrauding wealthy investors, but SEC and FBI zero down on their empire.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">23. 12 Years a Slave (2013)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Chiwetel-Ejiofor-12-Years-a-Slave.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 759px) 100vw, 759px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Chiwetel-Ejiofor-12-Years-a-Slave.jpg 759w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Chiwetel-Ejiofor-12-Years-a-Slave-300x207.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Chiwetel-Ejiofor-12-Years-a-Slave-261x180.jpg 261w\" alt=\"12 Years a Slave (2013)\" width=\"759\" height=\"524\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Many years before the civil war, a free black man from Newyork is kidnaped and sold into slavery to the North side of the country. Subjected to cruelty from one owner and kindness from another, 12 years of his life turn into an ordeal. It was broken when he gets discovered by an abolitionist from Canda, who takes him back to his free life.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">24. 42 (2013)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/42-2013-1024x603.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/42-2013-1024x603.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/42-2013-300x177.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/42-2013-768x452.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/42-2013-306x180.jpg 306w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/42-2013.jpg 1550w\" alt=\"42 (2013)\" width=\"640\" height=\"377\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">When talent silences all critics. Branch Rickey, a football team manager, hires Jackie Robinson who is black, by going against everyone. The heroic act is met with criticism from Press and the general public, but both of them prefer to respond only through Jackie&rsquo;s talent.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">25. The Imitation Game (2014)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Imitation-Game-2014-1024x683.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Imitation-Game-2014-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Imitation-Game-2014-300x200.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Imitation-Game-2014-768x512.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Imitation-Game-2014-270x180.jpg 270w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Imitation-Game-2014-84x55.jpg 84w\" alt=\"The Imitation Game (2014)\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Based on the story of Father of Cryptanalysis, the British Intelligence Agency MI6 hires Alan Turing to crack Nazi codes including Enigma, which was believed that no one could decipher it. Turing along with his team achieved success when they were able to beat Enigma, but in the year 1952, Turing faced disgrace for being a Homosexual and was thrown into prison.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">26. The Theory of Everything (2014)</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Theory-of-Everything-2014-1024x576.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Theory-of-Everything-2014-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Theory-of-Everything-2014-300x169.jpg 300w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Theory-of-Everything-2014-768x432.jpg 768w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Theory-of-Everything-2014-320x180.jpg 320w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Theory-of-Everything-2014-600x338.jpg 600w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Theory-of-Everything-2014-200x113.jpg 200w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Theory-of-Everything-2014-195x110.jpg 195w, https://moviesdrop.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Theory-of-Everything-2014.jpg 1280w\" alt=\"The Theory of Everything (2014)\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Based on the life of Stephen Hawking, the Theory Of Everything is a story about Stephen Hawking and his wife, Jane Wilde. At 21, Stephen realizes that he has neuron disease which is not curable, but he doesn&rsquo;t give up. Along with his wife, they both defy odds and make groundbreaking discoveries in the field of medicine and science.</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', 'Motivations', 'img/posts/post5baf7cce9d09c.png', 1, 'published', '2018-09-29 13:23:26.646228');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`post_id`, `title`, `post`, `category_id`, `image`, `author_id`, `status`, `post_date`) VALUES
(13, '29 Inspirational Quotes', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">29 Inspirational Quotes That Will Motivate You To A Successful Life</h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Here are my favorite inspirational quotes about life:</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">1) &ldquo;The Way Get Started Is To Quit Talking And Begin Doing.&rdquo; &ndash; Walt Disney</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This straight-to-business&nbsp;quote comes from the man who created the happiest place on earth &ndash; and a multibillion-dollar empire.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ctt.ec/ua7nt\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Click here to tweet this quote</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/walt-disney-the-best-way-to-get-started.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/walt-disney-the-best-way-to-get-started.png 640w, https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/walt-disney-the-best-way-to-get-started-300x252.png 300w\" alt=\"inspirational quote by Walt Disney over image of feet on stair case\" data-wp-pid=\"16563\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">2) &ldquo;The Pessimist Sees Difficulty In Every Opportunity. The Optimist Sees Opportunity In Every Difficulty.&rdquo; &ndash; Winston Churchill</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">When it comes to success quotes by famous people, Winston Churchill&rsquo;s inspirational words of wisdom always make the list.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://ctt.ec/Cquce\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Click here to tweet this quote</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/winston-churchill-the-pessimist-sees-difficulty.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/winston-churchill-the-pessimist-sees-difficulty.jpg 640w, https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/winston-churchill-the-pessimist-sees-difficulty-300x252.jpg 300w\" alt=\"inspirational sunset with quote by Winston Churchill about optimism in life\" data-wp-pid=\"16565\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">3) &ldquo;Don&rsquo;t Let Yesterday Take Up Too Much Of Today.&rdquo; &ndash; Will Rogers</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Will Rogers was an American actor, cowboy, columnist and social commentator who believed in keeping forward momentum.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://ctt.ec/O864m\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Click here to tweet this quote</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/will-rodger-dont-let-yesterday.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/will-rodger-dont-let-yesterday.png 640w, https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/will-rodger-dont-let-yesterday-300x252.png 300w\" alt=\"night skyline with inspirational quote by Will Rogers \" data-wp-pid=\"16564\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">4) &ldquo;You Learn More From Failure Than From Success. Don&rsquo;t Let It Stop You. Failure Builds Character.&rdquo; &ndash; Unknown</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">When you replace &lsquo;lose&rsquo; with &lsquo;learn&rsquo; in your vocabulary, the thought of failure becomes less daunting and lets you focus on growth.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ctt.ec/TzcVE\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Click here to tweet this</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/you-learn-more-from-failure.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/you-learn-more-from-failure.png 640w, https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/you-learn-more-from-failure-300x252.png 300w\" alt=\"sunrise with motivational success quote about learning from failure \" data-wp-pid=\"16566\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Click the link button below to sign up for my daily quotes email that includes many more of my most popular&nbsp;inspirational quotes, delivered to your inbox daily. It will empower and motivate you to take action, create success, and enjoy life &ndash; no matter how tough it gets.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">5) &ldquo;It&rsquo;s Not Whether You Get Knocked Down, It&rsquo;s Whether You Get Up.&rdquo; &ndash; Inspirational Quote By Vince Lombardi</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Vince Lombardi was an American football hero who&rsquo;s uplifting words frequently make it onto Top 10 Inspirational Quotes lists.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ctt.ec/dRa67\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Click here to tweet this quote</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/vince-lombardi-its-not-whether-you-get-knocked-down.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/vince-lombardi-its-not-whether-you-get-knocked-down.jpg 640w, https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/vince-lombardi-its-not-whether-you-get-knocked-down-300x252.jpg 300w\" alt=\"inspirational quote by vince lombardi on image of man on mountainside\" data-wp-pid=\"16562\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">6) &ldquo;If You Are Working On Something That You Really Care About, You Don&rsquo;t Have To Be Pushed. The Vision Pulls You.&rdquo; &ndash; Steve Jobs</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Steve Jobs truly captured some of the wisdom of life in this statement. Do&nbsp;that which you are passionate about and your work will feel effortless.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/steve-jobs-if-you-a-working-on-something.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/steve-jobs-if-you-a-working-on-something.png 640w, https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/steve-jobs-if-you-a-working-on-something-300x252.png 300w\" alt=\"motivational ocean view with Steve Jobs quote about working with your passion\" data-wp-pid=\"16561\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">7) &ldquo;People Who Are Crazy Enough To Think They Can Change The World, Are The Ones Who Do.&rdquo; &ndash; Rob Siltanen</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I believe this is one of the best quotes to live by because&nbsp;it&nbsp;reminds me to think without limits and never doubt my wildest thoughts.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/rob-siltanen-people-who-are-crazy-enough-to-change-the-world.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/rob-siltanen-people-who-are-crazy-enough-to-change-the-world.jpg 640w, https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/rob-siltanen-people-who-are-crazy-enough-to-change-the-world-300x252.jpg 300w\" alt=\"inspirational quote by Rob Siltanen on image of man jumping over a mountain peak\" data-wp-pid=\"16560\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">8) &ldquo;Failure Will Never Overtake Me If My Determination To Succeed Is Strong Enough.&rdquo; &ndash; Og Mandino</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There&rsquo;s a&nbsp;special place in my heart for these&nbsp;inspirational words. They remind me of&nbsp;my unwavering determination to become a motivational speaker.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/og-mandino-failure-will-never-overtake-me.jpg\" alt=\"og-mandino-failure-will-never-overtake-me\" data-wp-pid=\"16559\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">9) &ldquo;Entrepreneurs Are Great At Dealing With Uncertainty And Also Very Good At Minimizing Risk. That&rsquo;s The Classic Entrepreneur.&rdquo; &ndash; Mohnish Pabrai</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This line always puts a smile on my face because it alludes to&nbsp;the excitement of not knowing what to expect but seeing a possible&nbsp;life-changing&nbsp;outcome.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/mohnish-pabrai-entreprenuers-are-great-at-dealing-with-uncertainty.png\" alt=\"mohnish-pabrai-entreprenuers-are-great-at-dealing-with-uncertainty\" data-wp-pid=\"16558\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">10) &ldquo;We May Encounter Many Defeats But We Must Not Be Defeated.&rdquo; &ndash; Maya Angelou</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Maya Angelou was one of the top civil rights activists and embraced a spirit of positive thinking and sheer determination.<br /><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/maya-angelou-we-may-encounter-defeats-but-we-must-not-be-defeated.jpg\" alt=\"maya-angelou-we-may-encounter-defeats-but-we-must-not-be-defeated\" data-wp-pid=\"16557\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">11) &ldquo;Knowing Is Not Enough; We Must Apply. Wishing Is Not Enough; We Must Do.&rdquo; &ndash; Johann Wolfgang Von Goethe</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This piece of wisdom is one of my favorite quotes for students. It reminds us to apply what we learn and take action toward success, rather than waiting and hoping.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/johann-von-goethe-knowing-is-not-enough.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/johann-von-goethe-knowing-is-not-enough.png 640w, https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/johann-von-goethe-knowing-is-not-enough-300x252.png 300w\" alt=\"motivational life quote about success by Von Goethe\" data-wp-pid=\"16556\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">12) &ldquo;Imagine Your Life Is Perfect In Every Respect; What Would It Look Like?&rdquo; &ndash; Brian Tracy</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The exercise mentioned in this excerpt of my personal development philosophy is one of the keys to gaining clarity for what you really want in life. Start with a clear vision of your ideal life and happiness, then work backward to achieve it.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/imagine-your-life-is-perfect-in-every-respect.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/imagine-your-life-is-perfect-in-every-respect.png 640w, https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/imagine-your-life-is-perfect-in-every-respect-300x252.png 300w\" alt=\"inspirational quote by Brian Tracy on nature image\" data-wp-pid=\"16555\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">13) &ldquo;We Generate Fears While We Sit. We Overcome Them By Action.&rdquo; &ndash; Dr. Henry Link</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I love this pairing of quotation and image (below). Before we act, our imaginations often run wild, but when we move forward we often find the path ahead far less daunting than the horrifying version we had created in our minds.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/henry-link-we-generate-fears-while-we-sit.png\" alt=\"uplifting quote by Dr. Henry Link on image of man biking into a dark forest\" data-wp-pid=\"16554\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">14) &ldquo;Whether You Think You Can Or Think You Can&rsquo;t, You&rsquo;re Right.&rdquo; &ndash; Henry Ford</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Truly a quote to live by, the American captain of industry, Henry Ford, made this proclamation while reflecting on his life. He is still one of the wealthiest figures of the modern period. Ford also said,&nbsp;<em>&ldquo;Failure is simply the opportunity to begin again, this time more intelligently.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/henry-ford-whether-you-think-you-can.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/henry-ford-whether-you-think-you-can.jpg 640w, https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/henry-ford-whether-you-think-you-can-300x252.jpg 300w\" alt=\"inspirational words about success in life by Henry Ford on image of man\'s silhouette \" data-wp-pid=\"16553\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">15) &ldquo;Security Is Mostly A Superstition. Life Is Either A Daring Adventure Or Nothing.&rdquo; &ndash; Helen Keller</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Helen Keller is the author of this thought-provoking quote about life. I love her adventurous spirit and all or nothing attitude!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/hellen-keller-seurity-is-mostly-a-superstition.png\" alt=\"hellen-keller-seurity-is-mostly-a-superstition\" data-wp-pid=\"16552\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">16) &ldquo;The Man Who Has Confidence In Himself Gains The Confidence Of Others.&rdquo; &ndash; Hasidic Proverb</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">In this powerful Hasidic proverb, we learn an ancient truth that still holds up in modern times. The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.briantracy.com/catalog/the-science-of-self-confidence-training-kit\">power of self-confidence</a>&nbsp;is just as strong today as it was a long time ago. You can still change the thoughts of others by changing your thoughts about yourself.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/hasidic-proverb-the-man-who-has-confidence-in-himself.jpg\" alt=\"hasidic-proverb-the-man-who-has-confidence-in-himself\" data-wp-pid=\"16551\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">17) &ldquo;The Only Limit To Our Realization Of Tomorrow Will Be Our Doubts Of Today.&rdquo; &ndash; Franklin D. Roosevelt</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">F.D.R. famously alluded to the impact&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/personal-success/positive-attitude-happy-people-positive-thinking/\">positive thinking</a>&nbsp;can have on the world, stating that our doubts, or our self-limiting beliefs, were the only restraints on the possibilities of the future.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/franklin-roosevelt-limit-to-realization-of-tomorrow.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" srcset=\"https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/franklin-roosevelt-limit-to-realization-of-tomorrow.png 640w, https://www.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/franklin-roosevelt-limit-to-realization-of-tomorrow-300x252.png 300w\" alt=\"quote by Franklin D. Roosevelt about self doubt and positive thinking\" data-wp-pid=\"16550\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">18) &ldquo;Creativity Is Intelligence Having Fun.&rdquo; &ndash; Albert Einstein</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Albert Einstein authored this encouraging and uplifting quote. In just five words, he captured the essence of his intellectual philosophy and inspired others to embrace the creative process.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/einstein-creativity-is-intelligence-having-fun.png\" alt=\"einstein-creativity-is-intelligence-having-fun\" data-wp-pid=\"16549\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">19) &ldquo;What You Lack In Talent Can Be Made Up With Desire, Hustle And Giving 110% All The Time.&rdquo; &ndash; Don Zimmer</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Professional baseball player and coach, Don Zimmer dedicated 65 years to the sport. The wisdom he left behind implies that will power and dedication are just as important as ability. Again, alluding to the concept that success is formed in the mind before it is manifested in reality.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/don-zimmer-what-you-lack-in-talent.png\" alt=\"don-zimmer-what-you-lack-in-talent\" data-wp-pid=\"16548\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">20) &ldquo;Do What You Can With All You Have, Wherever You Are.&rdquo; &ndash; Theodore Roosevelt</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">At number twenty, we have one of the most famous quotes about life by Teddy Roosevelt, who served as President of the United States from 1901 to 1909. A true optimist, he believed in the value of always giving it your all, no matter what you have or where you are.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/do-what-you-can-with-all-you-have.png\" alt=\"do-what-you-can-with-all-you-have\" data-wp-pid=\"16547\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">21) &ldquo;Develop An &lsquo;Attitude Of Gratitude&rsquo;. Say Thank You To Everyone You Meet For Everything They Do For You.&rdquo; &ndash; Brian Tracy</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/develop-an-attitude-of-gratitude.png\" alt=\"develop-an-attitude-of-gratitude\" data-wp-pid=\"16546\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">22) &ldquo;You Are Never Too Old To Set Another Goal Or To Dream A New Dream.&rdquo; &ndash; C.S. Lewis</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/cs-lewis-never-too-old-to-set-another-goal.jpg\" alt=\"cs-lewis-never-too-old-to-set-another-goal\" data-wp-pid=\"16609\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">23) &ldquo;To See What Is Right And Not Do It Is A Lack Of Courage.&rdquo; &ndash; Confucious</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/confucious-to-see-what-is-right.png\" alt=\"confucious-to-see-what-is-right\" data-wp-pid=\"16544\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">24) &ldquo;Reading Is To The Mind, As Exercise Is To The Body.&rdquo; &ndash; Brian Tracy</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/brian-tracy-reading-is-to-the-mind.png\" alt=\"brian-tracy-reading-is-to-the-mind\" data-wp-pid=\"16543\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">25) &ldquo;Fake It Until You Make It! Act As If You Had All The Confidence You Require Until It Becomes Your Reality.&rdquo; &ndash; Brian Tracy</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/brian-tracy-fake-it-till-you-make-it.png\" alt=\"brian-tracy-fake-it-till-you-make-it\" data-wp-pid=\"16542\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">26) &ldquo;The Future Belongs To The Competent. Get Good, Get Better, Be The Best!&rdquo; &ndash; Success Quote By Brian Tracy</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 640px; height: auto; max-width: 640px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/quotes/the-future-belongs-to-the-competent.png\" alt=\"the-future-belongs-to-the-competent\" data-wp-pid=\"16599\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">27) &ldquo;For Every Reason It&rsquo;s Not Possible, There Are Hundreds Of People Who Have Faced The Same Circumstances And Succeeded.&rdquo; &ndash; Jack Canfield</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: auto; max-width: 600px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/07130213/Jack-Canfield-For-every-reason-inspirational-quote.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/07130213/Jack-Canfield-For-every-reason-inspirational-quote.png 600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/07130213/Jack-Canfield-For-every-reason-inspirational-quote-300x300.png 300w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/07130213/Jack-Canfield-For-every-reason-inspirational-quote-200x200.png 200w\" alt=\"Jack-Canfield-For-every-reason-inspirational-quote\" data-wp-pid=\"19244\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">28) &ldquo;Things Work Out Best For Those Who Make The Best Of How Things Work Out.&rdquo; &ndash; Positive Quote By John Wooden</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"width: 600px; height: auto; max-width: 600px;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/07130220/John-Wooden-Things-Work-out-inspirational-quote.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/07130220/John-Wooden-Things-Work-out-inspirational-quote.png 600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/07130220/John-Wooden-Things-Work-out-inspirational-quote-300x300.png 300w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/07130220/John-Wooden-Things-Work-out-inspirational-quote-200x200.png 200w\" alt=\"John-Wooden-Things-Work-out-inspirational-quote\" data-wp-pid=\"19245\" /></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">29) &ldquo;A Room Without Books Is Like A Body Without A Soul.&rdquo; &ndash; Marcus Tullius Cicero</h3>\r\n<p><img style=\"width: 600px; height: auto; max-width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/07130224/Marcus-Tullius-Cicero-a-room-without-books-inspirational-quote.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/07130224/Marcus-Tullius-Cicero-a-room-without-books-inspirational-quote.png 600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/07130224/Marcus-Tullius-Cicero-a-room-without-books-inspirational-quote-300x300.png 300w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/media.briantracy.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/07130224/Marcus-Tullius-Cicero-a-room-without-books-inspirational-quote-200x200.png 200w\" alt=\"Marcus-Tullius-Cicero-a-room-without-books-inspirational-quote\" data-wp-pid=\"19246\" /></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', 'Motivations', 'img/posts/post5baf7f7cdc938.jpg', 1, 'published', '2018-09-29 13:31:03.951384');

